terminal.mojom defines TerminalHost (Start/Write/Resize/Subscribe) +
TerminalObserver (OnOutput/OnExit). SlayzoneTerminalHost is per-frame:
one pty per chrome://slayzone-terminal/ frame. SlayzoneTerminalUI owns
the host via std::unique_ptr, following the Phase 9 overlay pattern
(vs the per-BrowserView singleton pattern used in 7.1-7.6).

SidecarClient gets RegisterNotificationHandler(method, callback) so
terminal.output / terminal.exit JSON-RPC notifications emitted by the
sidecar's broadcaster reach the right host. A per-process TerminalRouter
(in slayzone_terminal_host.cc) owns a weak_ptr map id→host and
registers once on first use.

URL constants, binder, webui registry, and region_container all wired
for "terminal" region → chrome://slayzone-terminal/.
